WEBVTT

00:22.022 --> 00:25.608
-So, Copper River next week then?
- Sounds good.

00:25.692 --> 00:27.193
-Is that a promise?
-You bet.

00:27.277 --> 00:29.988
All right, fingers crossed.
Tell Theresa I said hi.

00:30.071 --> 00:31.448
Thanks. Will do, Love.

00:34.117 --> 00:35.285
<i> I'm an optimist.</i>

00:36.202 --> 00:38.872
<i>And that, Love, is why I'm gonna say,</i>

00:38.955 --> 00:41.791
<i>"I can't wait</i>
<i>to tell our story to our kids."</i>

00:43.460 --> 00:44.961
<i>I know, it's hardly begun,</i>

00:45.045 --> 00:46.838
<i>but it's how I've always been.</i>

00:47.422 --> 00:50.633
<i>Even as a kid, one glance from a girl</i>

00:50.717 --> 00:53.595
<i>and I was trying out</i>
<i>my last name with hers.</i>

00:54.387 --> 00:55.972
<i>I don't think that's wrong.</i>

00:56.056 --> 01:00.393
<i>I think love should come out of nowhere,</i>
<i>sweep you up completely.</i>

01:00.477 --> 01:04.022
<i>But let's not conflate optimism</i>
<i>with certitude.</i>

01:04.105 --> 01:06.316
<i>I've learned some hard lessons,</i>

01:06.399 --> 01:07.650
<i>fools do rush in.</i>

01:10.403 --> 01:13.156
<i>And I've been the fool more than once.</i>

01:15.408 --> 01:18.328
<i>If I'm honest, I saw red flags</i>

01:18.411 --> 01:19.621
<i>and explained them away.</i>

01:20.288 --> 01:22.332
<i>I wanted love so badly,</i>

01:22.874 --> 01:25.251
<i>which is why I have to see</i>
<i>with clear eyes now.</i>

01:25.335 --> 01:27.087
You know what?
I'm gonna wait for the kings.

01:27.170 --> 01:28.880
- Okay.
-Which is, like, soon?

01:29.339 --> 01:32.675
<i> Find those flags</i>
<i>before we've gone too far.</i>

01:33.760 --> 01:34.677
What's her name?

01:34.761 --> 01:35.804
-Cindy.
-Cindy?

01:35.887 --> 01:38.348
<i> And this isn't to say</i>
<i>I'm not optimistic, so...</i>

01:38.890 --> 01:41.726
<i>our story, I suppose it begins a week ago.</i>

01:44.104 --> 01:47.524
<i>♪ All this time I was trying to find ♪</i>

01:47.607 --> 01:50.902
<i>♪ Some drug to fill this hole ♪</i>

01:51.486 --> 01:55.698
<i>♪ It was my mistake to trust in fate ♪</i>

01:55.824 --> 01:58.952
<i>♪ To show me the way to go ♪</i>

01:59.119 --> 02:00.120
<i> I got here,</i>

02:00.203 --> 02:02.080
<i>and within minutes, I knew...</i>

02:02.580 --> 02:04.999
<i>I'm in a strange land.</i>

02:05.083 --> 02:06.543
<i>Duck-lipped,</i>

02:06.626 --> 02:10.004
<i>stoned, suspiciously happy lemmings</i>
<i>everywhere you look.</i>

02:10.880 --> 02:13.466
<i>This guy, LA in a nutshell:</i>

02:14.050 --> 02:16.469
<i>the Unabomber with a three-picture deal.</i>

02:17.554 --> 02:20.473
<i>Welcome to a city</i>
<i>where people trying to disappear</i>

02:20.557 --> 02:22.392
<i>aren't actually trying.</i>

02:22.475 --> 02:23.685
Can I get a selfie with you?

02:23.768 --> 02:24.769
Yeah, sure.

02:25.103 --> 02:26.146
<i> Poor guy.</i>

02:26.980 --> 02:28.940
<i>-Must really hate all the attention.</i>

02:29.065 --> 02:31.025
-All right, have a good one.
- Hendy, can I get one?

02:31.109 --> 02:32.694
<i> And then there was me,</i>

02:32.777 --> 02:36.739
<i>the one in four million</i>
<i>not wanting to be discovered.</i>

02:45.623 --> 02:46.583
All right.

02:46.708 --> 02:49.043
<i> Step one in my effort...</i>

02:49.502 --> 02:50.628
<i>tacos</i>

02:50.712 --> 02:52.088
<i>with a man with a means</i>

02:52.172 --> 02:55.258
<i>to bring a new, unlocatable me</i>
<i>into existence,</i>

02:55.341 --> 02:59.012
<i>at least according</i>
<i>to his carefully worded ad on Craigslist.</i>

02:59.095 --> 03:04.100
Ever think how basically everything now
is GMO frankenfood?

03:04.184 --> 03:06.019
Like-- like, what exactly

03:06.102 --> 03:08.938
is all of this hacked corn
doing to our epigenetics, right?

03:09.022 --> 03:12.609
<i> Apparently, California's got its</i>
<i>own brand of conspiracy theorists.</i>

03:12.692 --> 03:15.403
<i>Yes, take caution,</i>
<i>lest you have a less-clean liver.</i>

03:15.486 --> 03:18.698
...you can give pigs fresh air
so they don't even <i>need</i> antibiotics.

03:19.365 --> 03:20.366
Just a thought.

03:21.284 --> 03:23.328
-Cages are never the answer.
-Totally, never.

03:23.453 --> 03:25.371
So,
what I need--

03:25.455 --> 03:26.372
I got you.

03:26.664 --> 03:28.208
Get out, no trace.

03:28.291 --> 03:31.544
If I want to leave today, say--
say, to Mexico...

03:32.086 --> 03:33.463
Great choice.

03:33.546 --> 03:35.548
Food's cleaner, cheap,
you'll love living there.

03:35.632 --> 03:36.925
But I can't stay forever.

03:37.008 --> 03:38.343
I have unfinished business here.

03:38.426 --> 03:40.511
But would not recommend a return trip.

03:40.595 --> 03:43.306
<i> Getting out to escape Candace</i>
<i>was imperative,</i>

03:43.389 --> 03:45.767
<i>but so too was the option to return</i>

03:45.850 --> 03:47.685
<i>and actually deal with her</i>
<i>when I was ready.</i>

03:47.769 --> 03:49.479
What I need is something
more comprehensive.

03:49.562 --> 03:50.855
Okay.

03:50.939 --> 03:51.981
Here's the deal.

03:53.233 --> 03:57.403
Truly airtight, livable ID takes... years.

03:58.613 --> 04:00.281
The Will you see before you,

04:00.365 --> 04:03.743
I micro-tweezed
like a bonsai for a decade.

04:04.327 --> 04:05.328
I'm employable.

04:05.411 --> 04:08.248
Background check me,
good luck not dozing off.

04:08.331 --> 04:10.041
Actual face online?

04:10.124 --> 04:12.043
No, can't find it.

04:12.126 --> 04:14.963
But google me and I feel real.

04:16.256 --> 04:19.342
And that, my friend, is a labor of love

04:19.425 --> 04:21.386
far too intensive to even put a price on.

04:22.345 --> 04:23.388
Okay, I get it.

04:23.721 --> 04:25.598
I appreciate you can even help me at all.

04:26.307 --> 04:29.435
Uh, so do you have it with you or...?

04:29.519 --> 04:30.353
Follow me.

04:32.188 --> 04:35.316
<i> I realized</i>
<i>that with my Candace issues,</i>

04:35.400 --> 04:37.735
<i>buying what this guy had to offer</i>
<i>wasn't enough,</i>

04:37.819 --> 04:40.738
<i>and I didn't have ten years</i>
<i>to methodically sculpt a new identity.</i>

04:40.822 --> 04:43.616
You got the benefit
of being a white dude.

04:43.700 --> 04:46.369
No one <i>ever</i> suspects shit
when it's a white dude.

04:50.290 --> 04:53.001
<i> I realized I needed to </i>be<i> him.</i>

05:03.094 --> 05:06.764
<i> Will seems okay</i>
<i>for a guy who's been in a box for a week.</i>

05:07.724 --> 05:09.475
<i>Without Mr. Mooney's help</i>

05:09.559 --> 05:12.061
<i>it took two full days</i>
<i>to put this thing together.</i>

05:12.145 --> 05:14.772
<i>Stressful doing it</i>
<i>with Will watching me, tied up.</i>

05:14.856 --> 05:16.232
You should be so proud of yourself.

05:16.316 --> 05:17.900
<i>Three quarter-inch plexi's a beast.</i>

05:17.984 --> 05:20.653
<i>Yet those edges are a thing of beauty.</i>

05:20.737 --> 05:21.946
...attention to detail...

05:22.030 --> 05:24.115
<i>I gotta think Mooney would be impressed.</i>

05:24.198 --> 05:26.326
I'm guessing it represents
more to you too.

05:27.910 --> 05:29.162
Safe space, perhaps?

05:29.620 --> 05:32.123
One you felt you needed
as a child for protection--

05:32.206 --> 05:34.876
I know everyone in this town
likes to talk about their feelings,

05:35.752 --> 05:37.337
so if you want a therapy session...

05:39.255 --> 05:40.214
tell me about Jasper.

05:40.923 --> 05:42.008
Look at you now.

05:42.717 --> 05:45.345
Able to put yourself on the outside,

05:45.428 --> 05:46.763
that must be so empowering--

05:46.846 --> 05:48.556
Who... is Jasper?

05:49.891 --> 05:50.850
Come on.

05:50.933 --> 05:52.769
He said you have something of his.

05:53.519 --> 05:54.771
He's looking for me.

05:55.313 --> 05:57.982
-Cannot keep me in here, Joe.
-I told you, this is temporary.

05:58.066 --> 05:59.275
Then what is the plan?

05:59.359 --> 06:01.861
I'm-- Look, I didn't--
I'm-- I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

06:01.944 --> 06:03.404
I didn't-- I didn't think.

06:03.654 --> 06:04.781
I acted.

06:04.864 --> 06:06.032
It was an emergency.

06:06.115 --> 06:08.242
- You can let me out.
-That's great, I would love to.

06:08.326 --> 06:10.703
Let's just figure out a way
to do that safely for us both.

06:11.537 --> 06:14.374
As soon as Jasper goes away.

06:14.457 --> 06:15.958
See, you're not hearing me.

06:17.502 --> 06:18.628
This cage isn't great.

06:20.338 --> 06:21.381
I need light.

06:21.881 --> 06:23.216
I need my meds.

06:24.550 --> 06:26.219
This isn't gonna be good for you.

06:26.344 --> 06:29.597
If you want me to consider your needs...
just tell me what this guy wants.

06:32.850 --> 06:34.143
Jasper Krenn.

06:34.227 --> 06:37.063
Met him on what a layperson might term
"the dark web," all right?

06:37.146 --> 06:39.107
Not even a client.
I looked into the guy...

06:39.399 --> 06:41.067
didn't like, turned down the gig.

06:41.150 --> 06:42.610
So you've never even met?

06:42.860 --> 06:44.404
No.

06:44.695 --> 06:46.072
He doesn't know what I look like,

06:46.155 --> 06:48.783
so he won't know that you're just
some random asshole

06:48.866 --> 06:50.952
who hit me in the head with a brick
and stole my life,

06:51.035 --> 06:52.453
if that's what you're asking.

06:52.537 --> 06:53.996
Okay, okay.

06:54.997 --> 06:56.958
Okay, hold-- hold on, hold on. You...

06:58.668 --> 06:59.877
You charge a fee...

07:00.503 --> 07:01.504
in advance of meeting.

07:04.715 --> 07:06.467
You didn't give him his money back.

07:08.261 --> 07:10.430
That is probably correct.

07:10.513 --> 07:11.806
You have to pay him back.

07:13.141 --> 07:14.934
I'd love to help, but I spent it.

07:15.309 --> 07:18.354
And my earning potential
is somewhat curtailed by being in a cage.

07:19.188 --> 07:20.231
How much do you owe?

07:24.402 --> 07:27.488
<i> Three thousand dollars.</i>

07:27.572 --> 07:28.698
<i>It's no problem.</i>

07:28.781 --> 07:30.366
<i>It's just 2,700 more than I had</i>

07:30.450 --> 07:33.035
<i>due to the lack of planning</i>
<i>that preceded my departure.</i>

07:34.745 --> 07:36.164
<i>Teach a man to fish...</i>

07:36.664 --> 07:38.666
<i>you feed him for a lifetime.</i>

07:39.625 --> 07:42.628
<i>Teach him how to make a counterfeit book,</i>

07:42.712 --> 07:45.047
<i>and maybe, just maybe...</i>

07:45.673 --> 07:48.176
<i>he can cobble together</i>
<i>a little something worth...</i>

07:48.259 --> 07:49.260
Three grand.

07:50.511 --> 07:51.679
Best I can do.

07:54.390 --> 07:55.725
Three grand it is.

07:56.267 --> 07:57.894
<i> I'll admit, bar was low.</i>

07:57.977 --> 08:01.439
<i>Mooney would have thrown the thing</i>
<i>back at me, had me do it 50 more times.</i>

08:02.064 --> 08:06.110
<i>Fortunately, an LA bookseller</i>
<i>is practically an oxymoron.</i>

08:09.155 --> 08:13.784
<i>At least now I'd be able</i>
<i>to send this Jasper fella on his way,</i>

08:13.868 --> 08:15.161
<i>get back to our story:</i>

08:15.536 --> 08:16.662
<i>you...</i>

08:16.913 --> 08:18.873
<i>the person who may</i>

08:18.956 --> 08:22.084
<i>just make paying a $3,000 toll</i>

08:22.168 --> 08:23.920
<i>to stay in this urban Gomorrah</i>

08:24.003 --> 08:24.921
<i>worth it.</i>

08:25.588 --> 08:27.256
<i>If only you weren't such an early riser.</i>

08:28.716 --> 08:29.759
<i>It's becoming clear,</i>

08:30.176 --> 08:31.719
<i>the more I see of you,</i>

08:31.802 --> 08:35.223
<i>the harder it is to see you clearly.</i>

08:36.140 --> 08:37.558
<i>If I don't want to get hurt,</i>

08:37.642 --> 08:40.520
<i>I have to keep a distance</i>
<i>till I've done my due diligence.</i>

08:40.603 --> 08:41.479
Hey!

08:43.940 --> 08:45.816
You keep wandering off. Here.

08:45.900 --> 08:48.945
<i>Though that's hard</i>
<i>when you keep inviting me to things.</i>

08:49.028 --> 08:50.655
I just didn't want to get in your way.

08:50.738 --> 08:52.240
Oh, that's impossible.

08:53.824 --> 08:54.825
Wow!

08:54.951 --> 08:56.827
Look at that opah.

08:56.911 --> 08:58.871
-Is that Ecuadorian or local? Thank you.
- Local.

08:58.955 --> 09:02.166
I know you're making
all of this up to impress me.

09:02.250 --> 09:03.417
You don't have to try so hard.

09:03.501 --> 09:06.462
If you told me that fish was an alien,
I would believe you.

09:07.964 --> 09:10.007
No, that's why it's good
you took me up on this.

09:10.091 --> 09:11.300
For a guy who works at Anavrin,

09:11.384 --> 09:14.720
you sorely lack an understanding
of the pescatarian lifestyle.

09:14.804 --> 09:16.764
I'm a pescatarian ignoramus.

09:20.560 --> 09:22.270
Are you okay? You look a little...

09:22.812 --> 09:23.854
Mmm.

09:31.654 --> 09:33.364
-<i> No.</i>

09:33.447 --> 09:35.992
<i>Too soon, too much, too good.</i>

09:36.075 --> 09:38.619
Yeah, I just wanted to stop
thinking about it and just do it.

10:21.412 --> 10:22.371
Interested?

10:24.206 --> 10:25.416
Hate the idea?

10:25.499 --> 10:26.959
I'm sorry, what did you say?

10:28.127 --> 10:29.045
Lunch today.

10:29.420 --> 10:30.421
My friends.

10:31.547 --> 10:33.424
I think we should
just rip the Band-Aid off.

10:34.050 --> 10:36.594
They're very LA, but they're also great,

10:36.677 --> 10:38.763
and... they're important to me.

10:39.513 --> 10:40.431
So...

10:40.890 --> 10:43.017
<i> And now you want me to meet</i>
<i>your friends?</i>

10:43.100 --> 10:46.646
<i>I really, really need</i>
<i>a clinical distance. No.</i>

10:46.729 --> 10:47.563
I'd love to.

10:47.647 --> 10:48.522
<i> Shit.</i>

10:56.280 --> 10:57.907
Earth to Spock.

10:57.990 --> 10:59.075
Come in, Spock.

10:59.950 --> 11:01.661
Where'd you go, old sport?

11:02.161 --> 11:04.497
You had that look
like when Keanu sees the black cat.

11:05.039 --> 11:07.291
"Oh. Glitch in the Matrix."

11:07.375 --> 11:10.086
<i> We kissed and I saw the ghost</i>
<i>of Guinevere Beck,</i>

11:10.169 --> 11:11.879
<i>my Matrix </i>is<i> glitching.</i>

11:11.962 --> 11:13.089
Yeah.

11:13.381 --> 11:14.507
Yeah, uh, no.

11:14.590 --> 11:15.633
I'm-- I'm fine, thanks.

11:15.716 --> 11:16.676
You know what?

11:16.884 --> 11:18.969
Let's see here.

11:19.053 --> 11:22.890
How about we move the women's lit display?

11:22.973 --> 11:24.642
Like, why are we separating them?

11:24.725 --> 11:26.143
That's sexist.

11:26.227 --> 11:27.061
Right?

11:27.144 --> 11:31.148
And besides, I woke up
with a completely brilliant idea.

11:33.401 --> 11:34.652
-What's the idea?
-Movies.

11:35.027 --> 11:37.697
-On loop in-- in the bookstore.
- <i>Oh, no.</i>

11:37.780 --> 11:39.448
Movies that are-- wait for it...

11:40.282 --> 11:41.200
also books.

11:41.283 --> 11:43.327
<i> Kill it with fire.</i>

11:43.411 --> 11:44.412
It's a great idea.

11:44.495 --> 11:47.081
-Dope movies like <i>Pulp Fiction.</i>
-<i> Not based on a book.</i>

11:47.164 --> 11:48.999
-Whichever of the <i>Star Wars...</i>
-<i> Again--</i>

11:49.083 --> 11:50.876
<i>Fifty Shades,</i> obviously.

11:51.293 --> 11:53.546
<i> One for three, marginally.</i>

11:53.629 --> 11:57.049
We are gonna sell so many books,
it is going to blow your fucking mind.

11:57.133 --> 12:00.177
-Can't wait.
-So just come clean this up,

12:00.261 --> 12:01.470
set up the screen,

12:01.554 --> 12:04.223
and when it all looks so cute
you wanna fuck it,

12:04.849 --> 12:05.808
holla at your boy.

12:06.392 --> 12:07.351
Namaste.

12:11.522 --> 12:12.606
I'm sorry,

12:13.107 --> 12:14.650
did you think this was a real bookstore?

12:15.151 --> 12:16.444
Bless your heart.

12:17.111 --> 12:18.154
It's cute.

12:27.705 --> 12:29.081
Hey, Bettelheim?

12:30.666 --> 12:31.500
<i> Jasper.</i>

12:33.335 --> 12:35.713
He said that you had something
that you wanted to give back.

12:36.005 --> 12:37.423
<i> This is Jasper?</i>

12:37.506 --> 12:39.800
<i>He looks like a manager</i>
<i>at a comic book store.</i>

12:39.884 --> 12:41.093
Sorry, who you looking for?

12:41.552 --> 12:44.346
Well, you, Mr., uh, Will B.

12:44.972 --> 12:46.640
Girl at your apartment
said you worked here.

12:46.724 --> 12:48.476
Did she mention that I left word for you?

12:48.684 --> 12:51.145
I'm-- I'm sorry.  I'm Jasper.

12:51.228 --> 12:53.439
Oh, right. Man, I have been
having trouble reaching you.

12:53.522 --> 12:56.317
I'm sorry, my phone's been weird,
you know?

12:56.400 --> 12:57.777
But here, your money.

12:57.860 --> 12:58.778
Here.

13:02.573 --> 13:04.450
-It should all be there.
-All 50 grand?

13:05.451 --> 13:06.744
<i> I'm sorry, 50?!</i>

13:06.827 --> 13:08.704
That's some of it,
I got to liquidate the rest.

13:08.788 --> 13:10.706
Oh. Oh, it's okay.

13:11.040 --> 13:13.250
But I'll need it today.
Is that still all right?

13:14.084 --> 13:15.002
That's great.

13:15.878 --> 13:16.796
Perfect.

13:18.380 --> 13:19.715
Hey, one other thing, uh...

13:19.799 --> 13:20.758
-Sure.
-Check this out.

13:20.841 --> 13:22.092
-Wanna show you something.
-What?

13:23.302 --> 13:24.261
What are you doing?

13:27.556 --> 13:29.642
It's okay, it's okay. Squeeze hard.

13:29.725 --> 13:31.268
Right at the knuckle, a little higher.

13:31.352 --> 13:33.270
Good. Good, good, good, good good.

13:33.479 --> 13:34.396
Now...

13:34.939 --> 13:36.232
I'm gonna need you to...

13:36.315 --> 13:38.859
just gotta hold that for me.

13:38.943 --> 13:40.611
Great, and, uh...

13:41.111 --> 13:42.488
drop her in there.

13:42.571 --> 13:43.614
There you go.

13:44.240 --> 13:47.243
Now, over at St. Henry's
they have a fantastic microsurgeon,

13:47.326 --> 13:48.327
Dr. Daniel.

13:48.410 --> 13:50.371
As long as you're there
in the next 10, 12 hours,

13:50.454 --> 13:51.831
good chance it'll reattach.

13:52.122 --> 13:53.624
Provided you have this. So...

13:54.375 --> 13:56.335
give me a call
when you have the rest of the money.

13:56.710 --> 13:58.587
Probably sooner
better than later, I'd think.

13:59.421 --> 14:00.631
Good to finally meet you, Will.

14:07.263 --> 14:08.597
<i> This is bad.</i>

14:08.681 --> 14:10.891
<i>Easily leave-town bad.</i>

14:10.975 --> 14:14.645
<i>But this is your town, Love,</i>
<i>and I can't leave you.</i>

14:18.524 --> 14:21.193
It's 50 thousand, Will! It's not three!

14:22.069 --> 14:24.864
Can we please talk about
the <i>$47,000</i> discrepancy?

14:24.947 --> 14:26.824
Can we talk about my hand?

