28:47.684 --> 28:49.352
Hey, I really think
we need to talk.

28:49.936 --> 28:50.895
Oh.

28:51.938 --> 28:52.814
Hey.

28:53.398 --> 28:54.232
Hey.

28:55.525 --> 28:56.985
Oh, my God! What happened?

28:57.068 --> 28:58.236
Oh, it's-- it's nothing.

28:58.319 --> 29:00.029
-Oh, no, what did you do?
-No, it's fine.

29:00.113 --> 29:02.615
It's a cut, it's nothing.
What do you want to talk to me about?

29:07.245 --> 29:08.413
You lied to me.

29:09.289 --> 29:10.582
-What?
-Lunch.

29:12.083 --> 29:12.917
Forty?

29:14.461 --> 29:17.213
He's a bad alibi. He's been telling me
everything since we were born.

29:17.881 --> 29:18.798
<i> Shit.</i>

29:18.882 --> 29:20.925
-Is Forty your brother?
-My twin brother.

29:21.760 --> 29:24.637
And you called him a dick,
which he can be,

29:24.929 --> 29:26.639
but you were also lying.

29:27.098 --> 29:28.308
You own Anavrin.

29:28.600 --> 29:32.645
<i> That's what I get for not trying</i>
<i>to find out everything about you first.</i>

29:32.729 --> 29:34.647
My parents own Anavrin.

29:35.106 --> 29:36.483
I just work there.

29:36.941 --> 29:39.903
I was trying not to instantly
complicate things

29:39.986 --> 29:41.237
by waiting to tell you.

29:41.404 --> 29:43.990
But you...
you complicated things by lying.

29:45.116 --> 29:46.159
Why would you lie?

29:46.242 --> 29:49.496
<i> So I could walk through</i>
<i>fire for you.</i>

29:49.579 --> 29:53.041
<i>So I could slay dragons to stay near you.</i>

29:53.124 --> 29:55.960
-I just-- I don't know you.
-Yet.

29:56.044 --> 29:58.213
-You don't know me.
-Yeah, well, apparently.

29:58.296 --> 29:59.714
Because I thought that we were...

30:02.592 --> 30:04.010
I mean, we kissed, Will.

30:04.093 --> 30:05.929
This is... This is not a good time.

30:06.012 --> 30:07.430
This is not good timing.

30:09.682 --> 30:10.975
This is about your ex, isn't it?

30:11.059 --> 30:11.893
-<i> Yes.</i>
-No.

30:14.479 --> 30:15.980
She <i>really</i> hurt you.

30:16.064 --> 30:17.607
<i> I can smell your shampoo,</i>

30:17.690 --> 30:20.610
<i>and nothing you're doing is making it</i>
<i>easier for me to see you clearly.</i>

30:20.693 --> 30:23.071
But guess what? My husband hurt me, too.

30:23.988 --> 30:25.490
Among other things, by dying.

30:25.824 --> 30:28.910
So, I understand why this is hard for you,

30:28.993 --> 30:31.663
but it's also why I just say things now.

30:33.540 --> 30:35.875
'Cause there was things
I was waiting to say to him.

30:37.585 --> 30:40.255
And I-- I don't know
if this is just a fling

30:40.338 --> 30:42.632
or something more, but either way...

30:43.341 --> 30:45.885
I think it's a mistake to do
the bullshit thing that you're doing.

30:45.969 --> 30:47.512
-No, it's not bullshit--
-Yes, it is!

30:47.595 --> 30:49.138
You don't need to run away.

30:49.639 --> 30:50.765
Please, no.

30:51.683 --> 30:52.600
-Stop.
-You can--

30:52.684 --> 30:54.060
Please! Stop!

30:55.520 --> 30:56.646
Just stop!

31:03.778 --> 31:04.654
Okay.

31:05.738 --> 31:06.906
You don't need to yell.

31:07.866 --> 31:08.908
Ever.

31:12.620 --> 31:14.122
I liked you.

31:19.294 --> 31:20.211
This sucks.

31:24.007 --> 31:25.383
You're bleeding again.

31:31.806 --> 31:33.016
Why are you here?

31:33.099 --> 31:35.852
You've actually lost
a lot of blood today, Joe.

31:35.935 --> 31:36.853
Is that what you are?

31:38.271 --> 31:39.188
My lost blood?

31:39.522 --> 31:41.065
Really all-in on this one.

31:41.649 --> 31:43.067
I guess that's you, right?

31:43.735 --> 31:45.320
See a girl once.

31:45.570 --> 31:46.905
I'm-- I'm trying...

31:47.488 --> 31:49.115
to do it right this time.

31:49.198 --> 31:50.325
As opposed to with me.

31:52.368 --> 31:54.621
What went wrong with me, Joe?

31:55.997 --> 31:57.540
We both know what happened.

31:57.624 --> 31:58.958
You can haunt me forever,

31:59.042 --> 32:02.837
you will never get me to say
I didn't do everything I could for you...

32:03.379 --> 32:05.256
-for us.
-Look at me, Joe.

32:05.340 --> 32:06.716
-No, you are not--
-Look at me.

32:06.799 --> 32:09.344
You are not here.
I am not arguing with you!

32:27.362 --> 32:28.613
Hey, Jasper, yeah.

32:30.198 --> 32:31.532
Yes, it's Will.

32:31.616 --> 32:33.076
I am on my way.

32:35.370 --> 32:36.913
Thank you for coming. Is that my...?

32:36.996 --> 32:38.998
Perfectly preserved
and anxious to get back to Daddy.

32:39.082 --> 32:40.291
Great. It's right in here.

32:43.002 --> 32:43.878
Look...

32:46.923 --> 32:48.549
I am not Will Bettelheim.

32:51.469 --> 32:52.679
-This is.

32:55.306 --> 32:57.141
Well, this is a first for me.

33:00.144 --> 33:01.688
My name is Joe Goldberg.

33:02.730 --> 33:04.023
I just needed his name

33:04.107 --> 33:06.234
and his life for a little while.

33:06.317 --> 33:08.778
So you put him in
a Hannibal Lecter thing, I see that.

33:09.195 --> 33:11.572
I assume you realize
that you need psychiatric help?

33:11.656 --> 33:12.699
I'm not crazy, okay?

33:12.782 --> 33:15.743
My ex-girlfriend's stalking me
and this is the best I could come up with.

33:15.827 --> 33:17.954
But can I please have my finger?
'Cause this is Will.

33:18.371 --> 33:20.081
He took your money. Take him.

33:20.164 --> 33:22.041
Well, if you couldn't get it out of him...

33:22.583 --> 33:23.418
Right?

33:24.168 --> 33:25.086
I mean...

33:27.755 --> 33:28.715
You sure, now?

33:31.384 --> 33:33.011
-You ain't got it?
-Please don't.

33:33.678 --> 33:35.638
You don't have to do this.
You don't have to--

34:10.882 --> 34:12.008
You see, Joe?

34:15.887 --> 34:16.763
No.

34:16.888 --> 34:17.972
You don't understand.

34:18.056 --> 34:19.015
But I do.

34:20.850 --> 34:23.227
I'm trying to survive.
He wanted to hurt me.

34:24.103 --> 34:25.146
Well, you hurt him.

34:27.482 --> 34:28.608
And you hurt me.

34:32.820 --> 34:33.738
I loved you.

34:34.447 --> 34:36.657
-More than I've ever--
-Then you hurt me.

34:49.378 --> 34:50.797
Look at me, Joe.

34:57.720 --> 34:58.679
Sometimes...

35:00.098 --> 35:01.682
we hurt the one we love.

35:02.183 --> 35:03.017
Right?

35:05.686 --> 35:07.772
You're not afraid Love will hurt you.

35:10.983 --> 35:13.444
You're afraid you'll hurt her.

35:17.490 --> 35:18.407
I'm sorry.

35:22.537 --> 35:23.788
I'm so sorry.

35:28.209 --> 35:29.752
No. Please stay.

35:30.545 --> 35:31.546
Please.

35:32.421 --> 35:33.381
Stay.

35:38.427 --> 35:39.554
I'm sorry.

35:40.304 --> 35:41.514
I'm so sorry.

35:56.154 --> 35:57.613
<i> Hendy was right.</i>

35:58.364 --> 36:00.867
<i>Dr. Daniel, one impressive microsurgeon.</i>

36:00.950 --> 36:02.535
<i>Thank goodness for these pain pills.</i>

36:02.618 --> 36:05.329
<i>They're gonna block out</i>
<i>more than one type of pain tonight.</i>

36:06.414 --> 36:09.250
<i>Knocking out Anavrin's security cameras</i>
<i>will cover up another.</i>

36:16.048 --> 36:19.927
<i> Sometimes I wonder</i>
<i>if I understand love at all.</i>

36:20.887 --> 36:22.597
<i>The thing transforms us.</i>

36:22.680 --> 36:24.265
<i>But into what?</i>

36:24.807 --> 36:29.103
<i>Love turned me into something else</i>
<i>back then with Beck.</i>

36:35.151 --> 36:36.319
<i>My hope now...</i>

36:37.570 --> 36:40.031
<i>is that you can turn me</i>
<i>into something better.</i>

36:42.033 --> 36:43.451
<i>Because of this is all I am,</i>

36:43.534 --> 36:46.537
<i>I may as well turn myself into Candace.</i>

36:53.669 --> 36:57.423
<i>♪ All of your love</i>
<i>Give me your love, give me your love ♪</i>

36:58.257 --> 37:02.303
<i>♪ Give me your blood</i>
<i>Give me your blood, give me your blood ♪</i>

37:03.012 --> 37:04.430
<i>♪ It's all that I want... ♪</i>

37:20.988 --> 37:24.450
<i>♪ Give me your blood</i>
<i>until I want no more... ♪</i>

37:30.665 --> 37:34.043
<i>♪ Anything else of the world before... ♪</i>

37:40.049 --> 37:44.011
<i>♪ Give me your blood</i>
<i>till I want no more ♪</i>

37:44.762 --> 37:48.975
<i>♪ Give me your blood</i>
<i>until I can't remember ♪</i>

37:50.101 --> 37:53.604
<i>-♪ Anything else of the world before ♪</i>

38:37.356 --> 38:38.232
Hey.

38:38.941 --> 38:41.068
Wow, it smells amazing in here.

38:45.031 --> 38:46.866
I did not just make you an entire meal.

38:46.949 --> 38:48.451
I am angry and embarrassed

38:48.534 --> 38:50.494
and I shouldn't have texted you back.

38:50.578 --> 38:51.620
I just...

38:52.455 --> 38:54.915
I was just also hungry, so I-- you know...

38:56.208 --> 38:57.585
I'm glad you kissed me.

38:59.670 --> 39:01.213
It did not seem like it.

39:01.297 --> 39:02.173
I was.

39:02.715 --> 39:03.674
I was also freaked out,

39:03.758 --> 39:06.260
not because you did it,
but because of how it felt.

39:06.552 --> 39:07.720
I didn't expect...

39:08.929 --> 39:10.056
-you.

39:10.556 --> 39:11.390
This.

39:11.932 --> 39:12.892
I wasn't looking...

39:13.851 --> 39:14.852
for this.

39:15.102 --> 39:16.562
I want it, but I can't...

39:17.730 --> 39:18.814
have it...

39:19.565 --> 39:21.067
right now with you...

39:22.193 --> 39:23.402
or-- or anyone.

39:25.821 --> 39:27.073
She really hurt you, huh?

39:27.823 --> 39:28.699
Mm.

39:29.909 --> 39:30.785
No.

39:32.119 --> 39:33.996
No, I hurt her.

39:35.456 --> 39:36.624
I really hurt her.

39:37.958 --> 39:39.752
So you understand, I can't--

39:39.835 --> 39:41.045
Did you wanna hurt her?

39:42.713 --> 39:43.547
No.

39:44.965 --> 39:45.966
Of course not.

39:46.050 --> 39:49.553
So what I'm hearing is that two adults...

39:50.054 --> 39:51.680
both knowing the risks...

39:51.764 --> 39:53.015
I don't think she knew.

39:53.224 --> 39:56.310
Okay, well, you know,
none of us know anything.

39:56.394 --> 39:58.187
You know?
But you put on your big girl pants

39:58.270 --> 40:00.147
and we give things a shot.

40:00.356 --> 40:03.609
I have to believe that hurting her was
the last thing you wanted to do, right?

40:05.653 --> 40:07.238
-That was a question.
-Yeah, that's right.

40:07.321 --> 40:08.322
-Okay.
-Right.

40:08.489 --> 40:10.783
How about I take care of me...

40:11.409 --> 40:12.952
you take care of you...

40:14.453 --> 40:17.081
I try not to hurt you,
you try not to hurt me.

40:17.164 --> 40:18.624
You know, what else is there?

40:20.960 --> 40:21.919
I'm just...

40:23.838 --> 40:25.589
I'm-- I'm afraid.

40:31.470 --> 40:32.346
Yeah.

40:33.264 --> 40:34.682
Relationships are scary.

40:35.266 --> 40:39.311
You don't get all that goodness
and possibility with zero risk.

40:39.728 --> 40:41.063
But, Will...

40:43.441 --> 40:45.234
you cannot hurt me.

40:46.444 --> 40:48.320
<i> I want to believe that.</i>

40:51.449 --> 40:52.408
Okay.

40:54.702 --> 40:55.661
Thank you.

40:57.746 --> 40:59.290
I just...

41:00.332 --> 41:02.042
-Just come here.
-Okay.

41:02.501 --> 41:03.669
Look, to be honest,

41:03.752 --> 41:04.920
I feel...

41:06.297 --> 41:07.423
so shitty...

41:08.799 --> 41:10.259
about the way it went with her.

41:11.093 --> 41:11.927
So I can't...

41:12.553 --> 41:13.471
I can't...

41:14.013 --> 41:14.930
till she's...

41:15.389 --> 41:16.557
really gone.

41:18.559 --> 41:19.852
No, it's valid.

41:21.020 --> 41:22.062
Yeah, no, I...

41:22.563 --> 41:23.772
Okay, two things.

41:24.899 --> 41:25.733
One...

41:26.692 --> 41:27.693
friends.

41:28.194 --> 41:29.778
Okay, friends can be good.

41:30.154 --> 41:31.906
We can just call this a friendship.

41:32.531 --> 41:33.616
That might help.

41:33.699 --> 41:35.618
Okay, great.

41:36.410 --> 41:38.162
Poof, friends.

41:40.539 --> 41:41.415
And two...

41:42.833 --> 41:44.460
I felt the same way about James.

41:45.628 --> 41:49.006
And I don't want to sound corny,
but I did this thing,

41:49.089 --> 41:52.092
where I took a bunch of his stuff
and I put in a box and I...

41:52.760 --> 41:53.969
let it go in the ocean.

41:58.015 --> 41:59.683
I'm not really one to hold on to things.

41:59.767 --> 42:01.727
It's not...  Um...

42:03.395 --> 42:05.147
You could just, you know, write a note.

42:06.524 --> 42:07.483
A goodbye.

42:09.693 --> 42:11.195
Burn it.

42:11.737 --> 42:12.696
Something.

42:13.364 --> 42:14.448
And I would help you.

42:16.951 --> 42:18.369
Friends support each other.

42:19.620 --> 42:21.205
<i> Whatever you call us...</i>

42:22.081 --> 42:23.541
<i>-it feels right.</i>

42:24.708 --> 42:26.377
<i>Because we're an "us."</i>

42:29.338 --> 42:31.799
<i>And if we are an "us,"</i>

42:32.299 --> 42:34.593
<i>then, dare I say it...</i>

42:35.094 --> 42:35.928
<i>this...</i>

42:36.512 --> 42:38.556
<i>this is home for now.</i>

42:41.100 --> 42:43.185
<i>And I should probably be a good neighbor.</i>

42:44.937 --> 42:45.813
Oh...

42:46.897 --> 42:49.233
Try that guy.
These two are full and that one--

42:49.316 --> 42:50.568
Eats the quarters, yeah.

42:53.070 --> 42:54.613
You don't have to be all nice.

42:55.864 --> 42:58.117
I feel bad, like I did something.

42:58.200 --> 43:01.620
No, it's not you, you were just
in the line of fire when Henderson...

43:02.538 --> 43:05.499
We go back.
We met, like, eight years ago

43:05.583 --> 43:07.459
when I was dancing at this bar downtown.

43:09.086 --> 43:12.548
Not just to do it, but because I was
actually pursuing something.

43:13.382 --> 43:15.551
I wanted to be Carrie Fisher.
She's such a great writer.

43:16.218 --> 43:18.554
But I was stuck in Covina
and my mom was such a cunt,

43:18.637 --> 43:20.389
and one day, I was just like, "Fuck it.

43:20.472 --> 43:22.224
Let me get a fake ID and get out of here

43:22.308 --> 43:23.559
and go follow my dreams."

43:24.018 --> 43:25.769
<i> It's hard to imagine her</i>
<i>with dreams.</i>

43:25.853 --> 43:26.687
Henderson was cool.

43:26.770 --> 43:30.357
He, like, gave me copies
of Syd Field, <i>Save the Cat.</i>

43:31.609 --> 43:33.444
And he was like, "You're actually good,"

43:33.527 --> 43:34.612
which nobody ever...

43:39.533 --> 43:41.076
And I had heard, or whatever,

43:41.160 --> 43:43.329
that he had young girls around,

43:43.412 --> 43:46.540
but I just thought
I was talented and special.

43:47.458 --> 43:49.335
One day, I was at his place,

43:49.418 --> 43:52.338
and I had, like, three sips of beer,

43:52.755 --> 43:54.798
and I got so fucked up.

43:56.592 --> 43:58.093
Eight years ago? You were, like--

43:58.177 --> 43:59.386
Seventeen.

44:00.137 --> 44:02.097
Anyway, I remember being like,

44:02.181 --> 44:03.599
"How is it ten p.m.?"

44:03.682 --> 44:05.976
And I look down and...

44:06.685 --> 44:08.562
my skirt was pulled up.

44:10.147 --> 44:11.732
So you're saying Henderson--

44:11.815 --> 44:13.567
Or, hey, maybe my skirt just rode up.

44:15.319 --> 44:16.570
Have you ever tried...?

44:17.029 --> 44:18.781
To what? Tell anyone? No.

44:19.365 --> 44:20.324
Who?

44:20.407 --> 44:22.951
I tried to do a story years later,
but nobody would talk to me.

44:23.035 --> 44:24.995
Guess why? They're all like I was.

44:25.496 --> 44:26.413
Underage...

44:26.872 --> 44:27.748
strippers...

44:28.123 --> 44:29.166
not white...

44:29.792 --> 44:31.168
The world would eat them alive.

44:33.212 --> 44:35.422
And that's why I don't lose
a drop of sleep

44:35.506 --> 44:37.174
on any of these motherfuckers
I write about.

44:37.257 --> 44:38.342
They all deserve it.

44:39.218 --> 44:42.763
My math says 49% of humanity
deserves to die in a fire.

44:45.641 --> 44:48.060
Don't do that. You, like...

44:48.560 --> 44:50.604
You nod as if you're somehow
not one of them.

44:51.105 --> 44:53.357
Well, let me give you the gift of honesty.

44:53.649 --> 44:54.525
You...

44:54.942 --> 44:57.277
act nice because you're not.

44:57.986 --> 45:00.239
And I may not know
what kind of bad you are...

45:01.407 --> 45:03.158
but I got my radar the hard way.

45:03.992 --> 45:04.827
So...

45:05.953 --> 45:08.288
stay the fuck away from me
and my sister, okay?

45:10.624 --> 45:11.834
Have a fantastic day.

45:29.685 --> 45:31.103
Tell me I didn't eat those.

45:34.022 --> 45:35.065
Do you know...

45:35.733 --> 45:38.652
how much oxidative stress
those things put on your body?

45:39.611 --> 45:41.572
I'm guessing a shower
is out of the question?

45:57.963 --> 45:59.923
Did you say Jasper came around?

46:00.507 --> 46:01.467
I paid the man.

46:01.633 --> 46:03.010
And he went on his way.

46:05.095 --> 46:07.890
If things were different,
I'd say I owe you 50 grand.

46:07.973 --> 46:10.058
-Why? You got it laying around somewhere?
-Nice try.

46:10.976 --> 46:11.852
It's spent.

46:13.896 --> 46:15.773
-What were you thinking?
-Honestly...

46:18.525 --> 46:20.235
a little while ago I fell in love.

46:21.487 --> 46:22.529
And she needed help.

46:23.989 --> 46:25.032
So I just did it.

46:35.292 --> 46:37.336
You've been putting meds
in my drinks, huh?

46:37.419 --> 46:38.295
That's green juice.

46:39.588 --> 46:40.422
Thanks.

46:42.633 --> 46:44.760
Well, my current reality is...

46:45.135 --> 46:47.387
suboptimal, but even so,

46:47.471 --> 46:48.889
upgrade from where I was.

46:50.516 --> 46:52.851
At one point,
I thought I saw you murder a guy.

46:59.107 --> 46:59.942
Crazy town.

47:01.318 --> 47:02.528
Well, glad to have you back.

47:13.038 --> 47:15.082
<i> I guess it's goodbye, Beck.</i>

47:18.627 --> 47:19.461
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

47:20.754 --> 47:21.713
<i>I really am.</i>

47:23.757 --> 47:25.300
<i>Goodbye, you.</i>

47:30.180 --> 47:31.139
How did that feel?

47:33.892 --> 47:35.185
Like a good first step.

47:36.979 --> 47:40.023
<i>Still can't wait to tell our story</i>
<i>to our kids.</i>

47:40.816 --> 47:43.360
<i>How we decided to walk before we ran.</i>

47:44.027 --> 47:45.529
<i>Started out as friends.</i>

47:51.618 --> 47:52.494
<i>The past...</i>

47:53.370 --> 47:54.413
<i>is prologue.</i>

47:55.706 --> 47:58.083
<i>I made mistakes, yes.</i>

47:59.084 --> 48:00.961
<i>And I'll learn from them.</i>

48:02.754 --> 48:03.672
<i>Prove...</i>

48:04.381 --> 48:05.382
<i>I'm worthy...</i>

48:05.924 --> 48:06.800
<i>of you.</i>

48:16.768 --> 48:18.729
Hey, should I open another bottle?

48:30.490 --> 48:32.075
<i> I know we'll get there.</i>

